result.adr_address: 38 Hung Luen Rd, Whampoa Garden, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 38 Hung Luen Rd, Whampoa Garden, Hong Kong
result.name: Dockyard

reviews.text:
Come here at weekday is better than weekend. 
At weekday, you can enjoy the peaceful environment with good food.
At weekend , especially the afternoon, it’s really a disaster with many noisy and impolite people.
There is a band show from Fri to Sun, the songs are good, the atmosphere is better than day time.
Finally, the food are quite delicious here.
And you also can walk around and enjoy the sea view.

The Dockyard is cool because of the variety of food and beverages that they offer. It is well located and easy to get to, even though it's a little bit hidden. Interesting in the way it operates and they have pub games to play as well. Worth a shot.

Very nice place. The concept is interesting. 
The dishes are correct. I expected more diversity of foods and did not see any burger in the menu.
Plus the bar closed too early 10:15 pm. Sadly.
A really lovely selection of amazing food, great ambiance... Live music on Friday and Saturday nights just completed the picture so definitely is the best time to go
The food here used to be a lot better when it first opened. Great to see they stopped using plastic straws but they need to bring back the burger. It's a basic!

result.name: 百味村

reviews.text:
去左2次～真係好鐘意佢個環境。星期五六晚7-10有live music，氣氛一流。地方又夠大同舒適。就算D食物貴左DD，但分量味道不錯，再加上環境好，出門就看海，算物有所值。更何況冇入場費同加一。係個越南法包唔夠地道，同酒太貴。韓國炸雞👍可能因為嘉里酒店樓上餐廳有韓國主廚坐陣。星期五晚去人唔多又唔雜，好適合同朋友去hea。不過家庭比較多。總之將會係我同朋友的聚會點。😋😋 食完仲可以行行紅磡碼頭。

更新：D小朋友玩的時候尖叫真係好吵耳。😓😓 千萬要坐係遊戲區的柱後。

result.adr_address: 38號 Hung Luen Rd, Hung Hom Bay, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 38號 Hung Luen Rd, Hung Hom Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Kerry Hotel, Hong Kong

reviews.text: I really cannot say enough good things about The Kerry. Everything was absolutely perfect and we had such an incredible time here. The room was BEAUTIFUL and clean, and the staff was super friendly and unbelievably accommodating when we needed them a few times. Also, the Big Bay Cafe was SO GOOD!!! We had breakfast there every morning and did dinner there once; the food was impeccably delicious and the staff/service was on point. In fact it was so good that if I'm ever back in HK and not staying at the Kerry Hotel I would not hesitate to swing by the Big Bay Cafe for a meal or two!

Decent hotel and good food in room service. Some experiences were very bureaucratic - for instance I asked for a 30 min extension on room checkout and the lady was insistent that that cannot happen. At 1115 pm, we were told by the concierge that the bar is closed and last orders are taken. however when we went there, the bar was more than happy to accommodate us and get us food. So the quality of service greatly depended on who you spoke to

It's my favourite hotel and I travel a lot. This time I brought my 4 kids and wife who loved it! The views are magnificent as are the facilities. We used the Club Lounge which is highly recommended. Location is great with MTR a 5 minute walk.

Club room. Free room upgrade for my birthday. Room comes with club access - great evening  cocktails and amazing breakfast. Room and pool superb. Staff very helpful and hard working. This is our 3rd stay at Kerry and every stay is better than the last! Keep up the great work!

Nice overall. Housekeeping was.helpful to deliver the items promptly everyday. Receptionist were quick and fast.
2nd day make up room was left with only 1 towel left but it wasn't a big deal. Overall great stay!
